		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img alt="ready.jpg" src="http://www.troyandgay.com/archives/ready.jpg" width="200" border="0" /><br />
My friend Steve's friend Bill sent out (by way of our friend Terri) this very helpful "legend" to the "what to do in case of attack" brochure at <a href="http://www.ready.gov">Ready.gov</a>.  There must be a design company somewhere that specializes in the "emergency instructions in the back of airline seats".  <br /><br />
<img src="http://ready.gov/i/bio_vis_substance2.gif"><br />
Don't get so preoccupied with biological weapons that you forget to put on deodorant.<br />

Update: found <a href="http://www.idlewords.com/nuclear_blast.htm">the real source of this</a>.  brilliant <a href="http://www.idlewords.com/weblog.02.2003.html#115">idlewords blog</a>]]></content:encoded>
